radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bilateral dependent atelectasis; no pleural or pericardial effusion; dilated appendix measuring up to 1.2 cm in diameter with a thickened wall; a 4.4 x 2.8 cm hypodense structure in the left adnexa, possibly an adnexal cyst; no evidence of bowel obstruction; unremarkable spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands; symmetric kidney contrast uptake and excretion; loss of height of the superior L1 vertebral body with a prominent Schmorl's node.
